# Ancestry.com
**Category:** ventures  
**Domain:** genealogy / family history / DNA testing  
**Website:** https://www.ancestry.com

## Overview
Ancestry.com is the world’s largest for-profit genealogy company, offering a subscription‑based online platform for family history research, historical record access, and consumer DNA testing. Users can build family trees, search billions of digitized records (census, immigration, military, and vital records), and use autosomal DNA analysis to find genetic relatives and estimate ethnic origins.

Founded in 1983 as a publishing company, Ancestry.com pivoted to digital services in the 1990s and launched its DNA test in 2012. Today it holds one of the largest consumer DNA databases globally, with over 22 million tested users. The platform is used by hobbyists, professional genealogists, and law enforcement in limited cases for cold‑case investigations.

## Utah connection
Ancestry.com is headquartered in Lehi, Utah, and is a flagship company of Utah’s “Silicon Slopes” technology corridor. Its presence has helped establish the state as a hub for data‑intensive consumer services and has supported a local ecosystem of genealogy‑related startups and professional genealogists. The company also partners with the Family History Library and the Church of Jesus Christ of Latter‑day Saints on record access and preservation.

## Key people
